On the second of December the noose closes: Lucio dies with his last brigade around him, and the army photographs the body with the care of men preparing a receipt. For the ones coming down, it is done the slow way: a priest who owes Othón a favor, a clinic in Chilpancingo, bus tickets bought in threes. Not all of them want saving and not all of them are saved, but by spring there are young men repairing mimeographs who last year were cleaning rifles, and in the Montaña the Party's name is spoken with a new modifier: *los que bajaron por ellos*. The ones who went for them.

